<p><b>What does R 000 mean?</b> Unless otherwise stated all financial figures have been rounded off to the nearest one thousand rand (R'000).</p>
<p><b>How do you write a rand amount?</b> In South Africa the convention is to use the decimal comma to separate whole numbers from decimal fractions. We use spaces to separate groups of three digits. So we write one million rand as R1 000 000,00. This makes big numbers easier to read.</p>
